This paper is primarily focused on improving machine translation performance, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic noise to improve robustness, which involves training machine learning models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of subword models and character-level encoders, which are common techniques in NLP and machine learning, respectively, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of edit logs from Wikipedia, which involves analyzing large amounts of data, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of character-level variation, which is relevant to computer vision tasks such as optical character recognition (OCR), making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
